<br>
This was especially relevant with ezboard, I'm not sure how much better it will be with PhP. But it's not just the god-awful ezboard search engine. Right now, General EQ is trimmed to 4/11/03. There are about one months worth of posts saved. Compare with Class Balance and Bugs, where the oldest post is from 8/9/01-- sixteen months worth of posts.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Thank you Goladus, this is what I have been trying to use to justify as the reason for a Newbie and High End board, but haven't been able to state it in a way that I was satisfied with.<br>
<br>
If you combine all of those into the General Forum, then you end up with all posts being merely temporary.  Imagine if there were only 2 weeks of posts.  To me that is like losing your short term memory. Not everything can be written into a guide, many things are specific.<br>
<br>
The High End/Low End forums should be kept pretty quiet.<br>
<br>
Looking at the first 2 pages of General, these are the only posts I would put into either forum.<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>What AA abilities should I get next? <br>
Upgrades for my stuff! <br>
People who like to use rains<br>
Spell Casting Expertise? Does it really work? <br>
Flowing Thought Question <br>
Are mana pool improvement effects capped?</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> <br>
So, I'm looking at, maybe 3 per page. Over 20 pages. Which is approximately a month.  That means 3 Pages per month, or assuming a total of 20 pages, 6+ months of total questions.  My goal would be for posts to stick in the top 20 for a year (so that by the time they start to fade off, an expansion would be likely).  <br>
So, split into 2 forums, I see 3 questions I would add to the newbie forum, and 3 to the end game forum. <br>
<br>
The Newbie forum would probably end up with mostly the newbies asking questions of each other, and the few &quot;old dino's&quot; that will help newbies without insulting their intellect. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=artillis>Artillis</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist<BR>Enjoys Sheep Erotica</span><br>  Posts: 1811<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/10/03 7:27:17 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=26402.topic&index=83>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What can we do to improve the message boards?</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Looking at the first 2 pages of General, these are the only posts I would put into either forum.<br>
