<br>
OT Discussion<br>
Rant Forum<br>
Poster Made Polls<br>
<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
My personal opinion here on your list. You guys should consolidate as much as possible. I know you guys are really trying to be nice, but I'm certain pruning and moding this board can be a pain in the ass sometimes. Besides, who really has the time anymore.<br>
<br>
In any case, here's what I believe you should keep/ditch.<br>
<br>
--- General EQ Forums ---<br>
<br>
General EQ Discussion (Definitely keep this one)<br>
Class Balance and Class Bugs (Keep this)<br>
Equipment Discussion (Definitly keep this)<br>
Roleplaying Forum (This is good to keep)<br>
PvP Discussion (Get rid of this forum, EQ isn't a PvP game, and there are plenty of other forums/websites to discuss such things.)<br>
Soloing and Grouping Discussion (Consolidate this forum into something called Wizard Mechanics, chances are you're going to have published guides on how to quad kite anyway, and if the discussion does come up, it will be minor)<br>
AA and Spell Discussion (Throw this into Wizard Mechancis form or something too. Again, alot info will be available on the website.)<br>
The Library (read only)* (I'd probably ditch only if you plan to add the material to the main website, which I think would be a better plan)<br>
<br>
Main Wizard Quests* (Published on the Website?)<br>
General Quests (Leave this forum)<br>
Spell Locations (read only)* (Published on the Website?)<br>
<br>
--- Limited Access Forums ---<br>
<br>
I think you're inviting trouble by doing this, however; this strictly up to you guys.<br>
<br>
The Arcanist's Hall (Basically what the Tower was going to be with a new name)<br>
<br>
--- OT / Not EQ-Related Forums ---<br>
<br>
OT Discussion (I'm a huge fan of this forum, however; considering how much bandwidth is drawn from this forum alone, I don't feel it's right for you guys to have to host this. If anything, someone from these boards should start an OT forum and host it themselves with only a link here. Or, if you do decide to host it here, people should be forced to pay for it.)<br>
Rant Forum (I would ditch this forum completely, or make it a read only forum, and have it pruned every week. Anything that would be deemed out of scope for these boards would be moved to this area with a reason edited into the post. That way people don't think you just outright deleted the thread. This is waste of paid bandwidth.)<br>
Poster Made Polls (This is a complete waste of time, instead of time spent moderating too many forums, the mods could be making polls on the main site for everyone, perhaps one per week.)<br>
<br>
I look at it in terms of bandwidth and the time the mods spend doing this crap, for free none-the-less. Those who contribute to the boards shouldn't have to burden the weight of forums that drive the majority of bandwidth, that money should go towards site content, and forums contributing to EQ only.<br>
<br>
Cutting back on forums and making a kickass main website with periodic updates will yield lower cost, lower administration, and will be more helpful in the long run.  consolidating as much info as possible from the forums into the website should be the goal.  The message board gods seem less forgiving when it comes to bandwidth usage than say, if it was available on the website all the time.<br>
<br>
Oh yeah, ditch the use of that little description under the users name when they post, or at least moderate it. Focus the website and the forums more on EQ, instead of other less relevent things.<br>
<br>
-Drin- <p><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:medium;">The Secret of a good discussion is not to allow intelligent comments to go unquestioned.</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=rombusmindspire>Rombus Mindspire</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><table width=111><tr><td style=filter:glow(color=#6633FF strength=1);font-family:arial;font-weight;bold;font-size:'1pt' nowrap><font size=1 color=#FFFFFF face=Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif>Forum Tyrant<br><br>Fan Boi Extraordinaire<BR>Cought up in EverWars...<BR><a href=mailto:rombus@graffe.com style=text-decoration: none><u>Contact Rombus</u></font></td></tr></table></span><br>  Posts: 7037<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/15/03 10:59:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=26402.topic&index=95>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.tritonguild.com/rombus/sidepic.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What can we do to improve the message boards?</span><hr size=1> * = removed once website is up.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=tombsz>TombSZ</A></span><br